headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 40 points, Mikal Bridges had 23 and the Brooklyn Nets routed the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 136-121 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 40 points, Nets rout short-handed 76ers 136-121

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Another loss for Golden State drained the joy out of Stephen Curry's second career 60-point game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores season-high 60 points in Warriors' 141-134 OT loss to Hawks

headlines.description: — There is nothing complex about Domantas Sabonis' impressive consistency this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis, De’Aaron Fox lead Kings past Bulls for 123-115 victory

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 24 points and the Los Angeles Lakers pulled away down the stretch to beat New York 113-105 Saturday night, snapping the Knicks' nine-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: James, Lakers pull away for 113-105 win to end Knicks' nine-game winning streak

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo looked up in slight amazement when told Doc Rivers had just clinched coaching in the All-Star Game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doc Rivers' first win as Bucks coach means he'll lead East All-Stars after huge rally to beat Mavs

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — San Antonio Spurs center Victor Wembanyama has received a lot of attention during his stellar rookie season, but the Cleveland Cavaliers' big men wanted to remind everyone they are pretty good, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Mobley help Cavaliers stand tall against Wembanyama, Spurs for 5th straight win, 117-101
